column9: \"code_summary\": \" **Class: ProductFeatures**\\n\\n**Methods:**\\n\\n- **oauth2AndSamlLoginSupport()**: Implements code to support OAuth2 and SAML login.\\n\\n- **multipleIdentityProviderSupport()**: Implements code to support multiple identity providers for OAuth2 and SAML.\\n\\n- **userLoginCredentialManagement()**: Implements code to manage user login credentials.\\n\\n- **secureAndReliableLoginExperience()**: Implements code to ensure a secure and reliable login experience.\\n\\n- **handleHighVolumeOfLoginRequests()**: Implements code to handle a high volume of login requests.\\n\\n- **ensure247Availability()**: Implements code to ensure 24/7 availability.\\n\\n- **quickRecoveryFromFailures()**: Implements code to ensure quick recovery from failures.\\n\\n- **scalabilityToSupportGrowingNumberOfUsers()**: Implements code to ensure scalability to support a growing number of users.\\n\\n- **securityAgainstAttacks()**: Implements code to ensure security against attacks.\\n\\n**Main Method:**\\n\\n- **main(String[] args)**: Calls the methods to implement the product features.\"
column10: \"product_features\": \" **Product Features:**\\n\\n- OAuth2 and SAML login support\\n- Multiple identity provider support for OAuth2 and SAML\\n- User login credential management\\n- Secure and reliable login experience\\n- Ability to handle a high volume of login requests\\n- 24/7 availability\\n- Quick recovery from failures\\n- Scalability to support a growing number of users\\n- Security against attacks\"
column11: \"requirement_spec\": \" **User Requirements:**\\n\\n* The system shall allow users to log in using OAuth2 or SAML.\\n* The system shall support multiple identity providers for OAuth2 and SAML.\\n* The system shall allow users to manage their login credentials.\\n* The system shall provide a secure and reliable login experience.\\n\\n**Non-Functional Requirements:**\\n\\n* The system shall be able to handle a high volume of login requests.\\n* The system shall be available 24/7.\\n* The system shall be able to recover from failures quickly.\\n* The system shall be scalable to support a growing number of users.\\n* The system shall be secure against attacks.\\n\\n**Elaborate Requirement Specification:**\\n\\nThe system shall provide a login page that allows users to enter their credentials. The login page shall support both OAuth2 and SAML login.\\n\\nFor OAuth2 login
column12: the system shall redirect the user to the identity provider's login page. The identity provider shall authenticate the user and return an access token to the system. The system shall then use the access token to authenticate the user and create a session.\\n\\nFor SAML login
column13: the system shall initiate a SAML request to the identity provider. The identity provider shall authenticate the user and return a SAML assertion to the system. The system shall then use the SAML assertion to authenticate the user and create a session.\\n\\nThe system shall allow users to manage their login credentials. Users shall be able to change their passwords
column15: and enable or disable two-factor authentication.\\n\\nThe system shall provide a secure and reliable login experience. The system shall use industry-standard security protocols to protect user credentials. The system shall also be monitored for suspicious activity.\\n\\nThe system shall be able to handle a high volume of login requests. The system shall be able to process at least 1000 login requests per second.\\n\\nThe system shall be available 24/7. The system shall be designed to be highly available and resilient to failures.\\n\\nThe system shall be able to recover from failures quickly. The system shall be able to recover from a failure within 15 minutes.\\n\\nThe system shall be scalable to support a growing number of users. The system shall be able to support at least 100
column16: 000 users.\\n\\nThe system shall be secure against attacks. The system shall be designed to protect against common attacks

column22: \"functional_test_scenarios\": \" **Functional Test Scenarios:**\\n\\n**OAuth2 and SAML Login Support:**\\n\\n- Verify that users can successfully log in using OAuth2 and SAML.\\n- Verify that users can log in using multiple identity providers for OAuth2 and SAML.\\n- Verify that users can log in using their existing credentials from the identity provider.\\n- Verify that users can log in using their social media accounts.\\n\\n**User Login Credential Management:**\\n\\n- Verify that users can change their passwords.\\n- Verify that users can reset their passwords if they forget them.\\n- Verify that users can manage their login credentials securely.\\n\\n**Secure and Reliable Login Experience:**\\n\\n- Verify that the login process is secure and reliable.\\n- Verify that users' data is protected from unauthorized access.\\n- Verify that the login process is compliant with industry standards.\\n\\n**Ability to Handle a High Volume of Login Requests:**\\n\\n- Verify that the system can handle a high volume of login requests without any performance degradation.\\n- Verify that the system can scale to support a growing number of users.\\n\\n**24/7 Availability:**\\n\\n- Verify that the system is available 24/7.\\n- Verify that users can log in at any time of the day or night.\\n\\n**Quick Recovery from Failures:**\\n\\n- Verify that the system can quickly recover from failures.\\n- Verify that users can log in even if the system experiences a failure.\\n\\n**Scalability to Support a Growing Number of Users:**\\n\\n- Verify that the system can scale to support a growing number of users.\\n- Verify that the system can handle the increased load without any performance degradation.\\n\\n**Security against Attacks:**\\n\\n- Verify that the system is secure against attacks.\\n- Verify that users' data is protected from unauthorized access.\\n- Verify that the system is compliant with industry standards.\"}"
